        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3475298796" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10616639932643415672"><b>.The Spy Who Came In from the Cold</b> is John le Carre&apos;s first espionage novel. It is also the book that first brought him acclaim and several awards. And deservedly so. This Cold War story is set in London and East Germany in 1963. The twists and turns, the characters, the action, and the dialogue all felt very authentic. And, of course, it is brilliantly written. Fans of George Smiley will be disappointed because he is not in this novel but the other characters do him proud. He is mentioned by ot</span>
  <span id="freeText10616639932643415672" style="display:none"><b>.The Spy Who Came In from the Cold</b> is John le Carre's first espionage novel. It is also the book that first brought him acclaim and several awards. And deservedly so. This Cold War story is set in London and East Germany in 1963. The twists and turns, the characters, the action, and the dialogue all felt very authentic. And, of course, it is brilliantly written. Fans of George Smiley will be disappointed because he is not in this novel but the other characters do him proud. He is mentioned by other characters here and there.<br /><br />This is the third novel written by le Carre's novel. I started with le Carre's debut novel then moved on to his second and now the third. It has been interesting to read le Carre's at the beginning of his career and the progression from detective and murder mystery to Cold War espionage. I highly recommend these first three books for Smiley and le Carre fans.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10616639932643415672" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
