<div id="review_3694630593" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3694630593" />
    <a title="Dave Schaafsma" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/269235-dave-schaafsma"><img alt="Dave Schaafsma" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1610298533p2/269235.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3694630593?book_show_action=true">Dec 14, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Dave Schaafsma" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Dave Schaafsma" href="/user/show/269235-dave-schaafsma">Dave Schaafsma</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title=" 9780575001497" href="/book/show/272757.The_Spy_Who_Came_In_From_The_Cold">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3694630593" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12599492727935520294">RIP, John le Carr√©, 12/13/20, at 89. <br/><br/>I read this in the early seventies and was expecting something like James Bond, but discovered something far richer and darker, not &quot;just&quot; a spy novel but a beautifully novel about the state, about British intelligence, with no heroes. In the manner of Conrad, or Graham Greene, who also wrote spy books, and said it was the best spy novel he had ever read. I read this again a few years ago in order to see the 1965 film adaptation with Richard Burton, Claire Bl</span>
  <span id="freeText12599492727935520294" style="display:none">RIP, John le Carr√©, 12/13/20, at 89. <br /><br />I read this in the early seventies and was expecting something like James Bond, but discovered something far richer and darker, not "just" a spy novel but a beautifully novel about the state, about British intelligence, with no heroes. In the manner of Conrad, or Graham Greene, who also wrote spy books, and said it was the best spy novel he had ever read. I read this again a few years ago in order to see the 1965 film adaptation with Richard Burton, Claire Bloom and Oskar Werner.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12599492727935520294" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


