  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3965485322" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3965485322" />
    <a title="Vince" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/128225739-vince"><img alt="Vince" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1629724401p2/128225739.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3965485322?book_show_action=true">Apr 28, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Vince" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Vince" href="/user/show/128225739-vince">Vince</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3965485322" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5356290830632069924"><b>He met failure as one day he would probably meet death, with cynical resentment and the courage of a solitary</b><br/><br/>Spy novels are a tough nut to crack in my experience. It can be real confusing with all the spy lingo hurled at you. But on the other hand it&apos;s a lot of fun because John LeCarre gives you believable characters to latch on to guide you through the story. I&apos;m too much of a rube to give a synopsis on the plot but from what I gathered it&apos;s about an English agent, Alec Leamas, who goes on his </span>
  <span id="freeText5356290830632069924" style="display:none"><b>He met failure as one day he would probably meet death, with cynical resentment and the courage of a solitary</b><br /><br />Spy novels are a tough nut to crack in my experience. It can be real confusing with all the spy lingo hurled at you. But on the other hand it's a lot of fun because John LeCarre gives you believable characters to latch on to guide you through the story. I'm too much of a rube to give a synopsis on the plot but from what I gathered it's about an English agent, Alec Leamas, who goes on his last assignment to topple the head East German Intelligence. Everything else was quite hard to follow but I genuinely liked the characters. One final note: I'm still reeling from the ending. I had to pick my jaw up from the floor. 5 out 5</span>
  <a data-text-id="5356290830632069924" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


